what i am doing...
on terminal, write command
npm create vite@latest   
npm create vite@latest is a command to create a vite project using the latest version of vite12. Vite is a web development tool that allows fast and efficient development of modern web applications. The command will download the create-vite@latest packages and prompt the user to choose a project name and a template12. The template can be specified as an argument after the project name, such as --template react for a React project2


√ Project name: ... client
√ Select a framework: » React
√ Select a variant: » JavaScript + SWS
           //SWC is used to transform your JavaScript/TypeScript code into a format that the browser can understand. It replaces Babel and TypeScript in the build process, handling the transformation of your code.
cd client,   npm install
  //npm run dev


